The course promised hands-on experience building AI agents, which I was excited about. However, I spent a significant amount of time troubleshooting and updating various versions of tools like Flowise, which was frustrating and detracted from the core learning objectives. This maintenance-heavy aspect was not mentioned in the course description, which set inaccurate expectations. While the content on AI agents was insightful, the undisclosed technical overhead made the experience less enjoyable and slowed progress. I’d recommend the course clarify these requirements upfront to better prepare learners.

I changed my rating in spite of the issue described below which initially resulted in 1 start. I resolved it, with a lot of time wasted, but I am happier now and I enjoy the course a lot, now that I advance at a more reasonable pace. Aside from that issue, the course teaches great skills. I am still learning and I am not done, but I wanted to be fair and update my reviews. Here is the issue that I encountered and triggered 1 star review: Flowise cannot be installed correctly and its functionality is severely impared. I spent a lot of time installing Flowise again and again and different node.js versions until finally I was able to open it and work with it a little. Then, I could not make Marketplaces work (it opens blank). I spend again a lot of time switching between versions of Flowise, node.js, npm and until now I am not able to go forward with my course because of not being able to use marketplaces. It is inexcusable that the course mentions nothing about those issues and lets us fend for ourselves and waste a lot of time and in my case, after all that I am still unable to advance my course. I would love to learn these skills, but this is a waste of money, as I got stuck right at the beginning, wasted a lot of time trying to find solutions to these issues, and I cannot advance anymore.

This course stands above from the alternatives in this space on Udemy that I could find in 2024.
